{
  "texts": [
    "The Australian higher education sector has seen an increasing number of students and academics from overseas, many of whom are from non-English-speaking backgrounds (NESB) (Dang & Vu, 2020).",
    "This demographic shift in academia necessitates a more nuanced approach to how educators provide feedback to students.",
    "Research indicates that educators' written feedback practices are significantly influenced by their sociocultural and language backgrounds (Cheng & Zhang, 2021).",
    "Feedback, particularly the formative or 'feed-forward' type, is essential in guiding students in higher education to improve their learning performance, especially in writing and research.",
    "Feedback provides students with insights into their errors and on how to improve the expression and clarity of ideas (Starfield, 2019)."
  ]
}